<div class="post">
	<h2><a href="/posts/how-to-transform-xml-into-sql-statements-using-xslt:480f4dfe-e130-46ae-af2a-4429cbdd56cb">How to transform XML into SQL Statements using XSLT</a></h2>	<div class="posted-on">
		<p>Posted on 4/5/07 by 
		<a href="/tim">Tim Koschützki</a>				</p>
		<div class="thumb">
			<img alt="" src="/img/tim_thumb.jpg"/>		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="body">
				<p><a href="http://raphaelstolt.blogspot.com/">Raphael</a> has blogged about <a href="http://raphaelstolt.blogspot.com/2007/05/transforming-data-centered-xml-into-sql.html">How one can transform XML into SQL Statements using XSLT</a> today. The approach is quite easy-to-grasp and elegant, featured by many code snippets. I recommend reading it if you have ever thought about using an XSLT-centric approach for generating sql statements on the fly.</p>
<p><!--adsense#singlepost_banner468horiz--><br />
<img style="display: none;" src="http://debuggable.com/posts/tick/480f4dfe-e130-46ae-af2a-4429cbdd56cb"></p>
